# UI / Engine Isolation

UI and UX work (layout, styling, animations, presenter shell) must **not** alter audio timing, looper transport, or P2P signaling latency.

## Protected paths (no edits unless explicitly requested for engine work)

- `public/worklets/**`
- `lib/solo-looper-engine.ts`, `lib/looper-runway-scheduler.ts`, `lib/studio-metronome-pump.ts`
- `lib/kite-interval-graph.ts`, `lib/kite-interval-math.ts`, `lib/studio-bridge-webrtc.ts`
- `hooks/useKiteStudioEngine.ts` transport: `startSoloLooper`, `prepareSoloLooperForRecording`, `fireSoloLooperRecording`, `commitActiveRecording`, `handleEnterSoloStudio`, `ensureSoloLooperEngineBootstrapped`, P2P/grid pump callbacks
- `hooks/useKiteSyncEngine.ts`, `hooks/useKiteP2PTransport.ts`
- `hooks/useKiteStudioHost.ts` (AudioContext lifecycle)

## UI-safe zones

- `components/studio-bridge/**`, `components/kite-loop-v2/**` (presentation props only)
- CSS / Tailwind, static copy, non-engine presenter wiring

## If `app/studio-bridge/page.tsx` must change

- JSX and presenter aliases only
- No new `useEffect` RAF loops on the audio engine
- Do not reorder engine init or add transport logic
- Do not import engine internals beyond `useKiteStudioEngine` presenter API

## Red flags (reject in UI-only PRs)

- `performance.now()` or wall-clock math for musical transport
- `setTimeout` / `setInterval` / RAF for downbeats or loop boundaries
- `setStudioUiPhase("studio")` before solo engine bootstrap + warmup
- Extra per-frame `postMessage` to worklets during idle startup

Complements `.cursorrules` Rule of One and latency mandate.
